<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.71.e64345>
    bibo:endPage "316" ;
    bibo:journal "Vertebrate Zoology" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2021-05-13" ;
    bibo:startPage "253" ;
    bibo:volume "71" ;
    dc:creator "Deepak, V.; Narayanan, Surya; Mohapatra, Pratyush P.; Dutta, Sushil K.; Melvinselvan, Gnanaselvan; Khan, Ashaharraza; Mahlow, Kristin; Tillack, Frank" ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "Revealing two centuries of confusion: new insights on nomenclature and systematic position of Argyrogena fasciolata (Shaw, 1802) (auctt.), with description of a new species from India (Reptilia: Squamata: Colubridae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.71.e64345.figure3>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.71.e64345.figure8>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.71.e64345.figure4> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.71.e64345.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Lycodon fasciolatus comb. nov. A. Holotype of Coluber fasciolatus Shaw, 1802, as well as holotype of Coluber hebe Daudin, 1803, \" Nooni Paragoodoo \" reproduced from Russell (1796, pl. 21), B. uncollected live specimen from Rushikulya, Ganjam, Odisha state, India, and C. \" Nuhni Paragudih oder Russelsche Hofnatter \", rearranged sketch from Russell (1796, pl. 21) reproduced by Bechstein (1802, pl. 9, fig. 3)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/542385" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.71.e64345.figure8>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Platyceps plinii comb. nov. Previously unpublished original colour-painting from the Thomas Hardwicke collection of sketches (Volume II, sketch 63) kept in the Zoological Library of the Natural History Museum, London, U. K. (see also Smith 1943, p. 529). Reproduced with permission from the Natural History Museum, London, U. K." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/542390" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.71.e64345.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Lycodon fasciolatus comb. nov. Previously unpublished extract from a paper sheet with glued specimens from the 1904 collection of dried snake skins preliminarily attributed to Patrick Russell showing a specimen of the \" Nooni Paragoodoo \" kept in the herpetological collection of the Natural History Museum, London, U. K. (BMNH 1904.7.27.93)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/542386" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

